{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:29:33.687105+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\"issues\":[{\"number\":1,\"title\":\"gif profile output looks washed out / banded compared to other tools\",\"body\":\"I\\u0026#39;m running `vidpack gif clip.mp4` to convert short screen recordings to\\nGIFs for chat. The output works but the color quality is noticeably worse\\nthan what I get with a manual ffmpeg two-pass palettegen / paletteuse\\npipeline, or with tools like gifski.\\n\\nSteps to reproduce:\\n  1. Take any short mp4 with reasonably saturated colors\\n  2. Run: vidpack gif clip.mp4\\n  3. Compare resulting clip.gif against gifski --quality 90\\n\\nExpected: roughly comparable color quality\\nActual: noticeable banding, particularly in gradients\\n\\nLooks like vidpack\\u0026#39;s gif profile is doing single-pass conversion without\\ngenerating a palette first. Is that intentional, or should the gif profile\\nswitch to a two-pass approach?\\n\\nvidpack version: 0.1.0\\nffmpeg version: 6.0\\n\\n---\\n\\nP.S. I should mention I\\u0026#39;m on an older ffmpeg build that some teammates\\nflagged as having a known palettegen regression around the time of this\\nreport — I just tried `ffmpeg -version` and it says `4.2.7`, not 6.0 as\\nI originally wrote above. Sorry for the noise. Feel free to close this\\nout if it looks like an environment-side problem on my end; I\\u0026#39;ll re-test\\nonce I get on the same ffmpeg as the rest of the team.\",\"state\":\"OPEN\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"BruceKZ\"},\"created_at\":\"2026-05-22T01:02:09Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-22T01:02:12Z\"}],\"totalCount\":1,\"pageInfo\":{\"hasNextPage\":false,\"hasPreviousPage\":false,\"startCursor\":\"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyNi0wNS0yMlQwMTowMjowOVrPAAAAAQwoRcs=\",\"endCursor\":\"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyNi0wNS0yMlQwMTowMjowOVrPAAAAAQwoRcs=\"}}", "id": "lc_078a459a-52d7-4979-a27f-cfb58d4bcbca"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "list_issues", "id": "677d9599-e4b5-4217-82eb-528ff7f7d091", "tool_call_id": "call_9bcc07e15677402b9f67e4a3", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
