{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:29:53.979705+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 9c34a6ceca64494a1fd10d7b2c1290f7e62e2930)", "id": "lc_e69ad46f-996a-4dc4-abba-7547150c0bee"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"\"\"vidpack — profile-driven FFmpeg wrapper CLI.\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nfrom . import profiles, runner\n\n\ndef build_parser() -> argparse.ArgumentParser:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(prog=\"vidpack\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--version\", action=\"version\", version=\"vidpack 0.1.0\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"profile\", help=\"Profile name defined in profiles.toml\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"input\", help=\"Path to input media file\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"-o\", \"--output\", help=\"Output path (default: derived from input + profile container)\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--dry-run\", action=\"store_true\", help=\"Print the ffmpeg command without running it\")\n    return parser\n\n\ndef main(argv: list[str] | None = None) -> int:\n    args = build_parser().parse_args(argv)\n    profile = profiles.load_profile(args.profile)\n    input_path = Path(args.input)\n    output_path = Path(args.output) if args.output else input_path.with_suffix(f\".{profile['container']}\")\n\n    if output_path.exists() and not args.dry_run:\n        print(f\"error: output {output_path} already exists; refusing to overwrite\", file=sys.stderr)\n        return 2\n\n    cmd = runner.build_ffmpeg_command(profile, input_path, output_path)\n    if args.dry_run:\n        print(\" \".join(cmd))\n        return 0\n    return runner.run(cmd)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    sys.exit(main())\n", "id": "lc_10f5a221-8b85-4cfd-94cb-a5079ad41685"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "f2f87f31-13b6-49df-b5b0-693ded8d600f", "tool_call_id": "call_1c3584f62ac84559ae23be41", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:29:54.157480+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: ca886e6501062ae49242c9393da158c273a90050)", "id": "lc_46ea5e47-7e31-45b4-bf10-a1b2ac8fb9d3"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"\"\"Build and execute ffmpeg subprocess calls based on a profile dict.\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport subprocess\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n\ndef build_ffmpeg_command(profile: dict, input_path: Path, output_path: Path) -> list[str]:\n    \"\"\"Translate a profile dict into an ffmpeg argv list.\"\"\"\n    cmd = [\"ffmpeg\", \"-i\", str(input_path)]\n\n    container = profile[\"container\"]\n    if container == \"gif\":\n        # Single-pass palette generation. See profiles.toml note about quality.\n        fps = profile.get(\"fps\", 12)\n        scale = profile.get(\"scale\", \"480:-1\")\n        cmd += [\"-vf\", f\"fps={fps},scale={scale}:flags=lanczos\"]\n    else:\n        video_codec = profile[\"video_codec\"]\n        audio_codec = profile[\"audio_codec\"]\n        cmd += [\"-c:v\", video_codec, \"-c:a\", audio_codec]\n        if \"video_bitrate\" in profile:\n            cmd += [\"-b:v\", profile[\"video_bitrate\"]]\n        if \"crf\" in profile:\n            cmd += [\"-crf\", str(profile[\"crf\"])]\n        scale = profile.get(\"scale\")\n        if scale and scale != \"source\":\n            cmd += [\"-vf\", f\"scale={scale}\"]\n\n    cmd.append(str(output_path))\n    return cmd\n\n\ndef run(cmd: list[str]) -> int:\n    return subprocess.call(cmd)\n", "id": "lc_5dc05721-2c29-41a9-8ad2-99484dd7081b"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "9ab5f767-81bc-4fc3-a2c8-31838cad8747", "tool_call_id": "call_56414eea73aa40d39303c4e6", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:30:18.604889+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have a clear picture of the situation. Let me summarize my findings:\n\n**Issue #1** reports washed out / banded GIF output compared to tools like gifski or a manual two-pass palettegen/paletteuse pipeline.\n\n**Evidence from the codebase:**\n\n1. **`profiles.toml`** contains a comment explicitly documenting this as a known limitation:\n   > \"the gif profile currently uses a single-pass palette generation, which is convenient but produces noticeably worse quality than a proper two-pass palettegen / paletteuse pipeline. Known limitation; tracked in the issue tracker.\"\n\n2. **`runner.py`** confirms the gif path only applies `fps` and `scale` filters — no `palettegen`/`paletteuse` filters at all. The gif is encoded with ffmpeg's default color quantization, which naturally produces banding on saturated/gradient content.\n\n3. The reporter's **P.S.** mentions they were on ffmpeg 4.2.7 (not 6.0 as originally stated) and suggests closing if it's an environment problem. However, the quality gap is real and baked into the project's design — it's not version-specific.\n\n**Decision:** The issue accurately describes a known, documented limitation. The project's own code acknowledges this should be improved. I'll keep it open and confirm the diagnosis.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1259, "prompt_tokens": 8825, "total_tokens": 10084, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 562, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 7936, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0015106146, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0004152846, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00109533}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780864194-qHuTOg3MNynU7YdcTuxl", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3c7-166e-7ed2-ae7b-46995b0bad0b-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "add_issue_comment", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T10_R01_C03_A01", "issue_number": 1, "body": "Thanks for the report, @BruceKZ — this is a real, known limitation in the current codebase.\n\n**Diagnosis confirmed:** The gif profile in `runner.py` applies only `fps` and `scale` filters before writing the gif directly. There is no `palettegen`/`paletteuse` filter chain at all, so ffmpeg falls back to its default (naive) color quantization. That's the root cause of the banding you're seeing — it's not related to your ffmpeg version.\n\n`profiles.toml` already documents this:\n> \"the gif profile currently uses a single-pass palette generation, which is convenient but produces noticeably worse quality than a proper two-pass palettegen / paletteuse pipeline. Known limitation; tracked in the issue tracker.\"\n\nSo this issue is the canonical tracker for that improvement. Keeping it open.\n\nRegarding your P.S.: even though the ffmpeg 4.2.7 vs 6.0 discrepancy is a separate concern, the quality gap you observed would persist on any ffmpeg version until the gif pipeline switches to a proper two-pass approach (palettegen first, then paletteuse in the encode pass). That change would look something like:\n\n```\n# Pass 1: generate palette\nffmpeg -i input.mp4 -vf \"fps=12,scale=480:-1:flags=lanczos,palettegen\" palette.png\n\n# Pass 2: encode gif using that palette\nffmpeg -i input.mp4 -i palette.png -lavfi \"fps=12,scale=480:-1:flags=lanczos[x];[x][1:v]paletteuse\" output.gif\n```\n\nWorth keeping this open as a feature request to implement two-pass gif encoding in the runner."}, "id": "call_4cf595221fdb42c9affc8e8d", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8825, "output_tokens": 1259, "total_tokens": 10084, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 7936}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 562}}}}]}}}
